Test Result:

\xc2\xb7      \nFinish Gold test execution\non RHEL 7.3. Please visit HPQC for test details. Refer to the installation guide for\nthe BKC package installation

\xc2\xb7        There\nhave 2 IFWI bin files included in the BKC pkg: True Release Mode\nIFWI(No serial, no debug libraries) and Debug Mode IFWI. BKC function test\nis conducted on the True Release Mode IFWI and the cycling testing is conducted\non the Debug Mode IFWI

\xc2\xb7       \nSwitch\nto SKX H0 CPU this week

\n\n\n\n

    \xc2\xb7      \nPurley FPGA (RP Board: Neon City FPGA)

o  \nTotal test cases: 29; Passed test\ncases is 23 and pass rate is 79.31%. 

o  \nTest coverage:  

SKX-FPGA H0 VIS/LBG B1 with True Release Mode IFWI: Run full BKC test case, P&P test

\n\n

SKX-FPGA H0 VIS/LBG B1 with Debug Mode IFWI: Run Power cycling\ntest.

Key Workaround (detail guide is here)

\n\n

Please use PCIe Video card\ninstead of onboard BMC video due to known BMC issue

\n\n

 

Pedigree and Board\nJumper Settings: guide

\n\n\n\n

Note: Only mandatory and necessary optional rework\nis implemented by BKC team

Mandatory rework FPGA JTAG chain missing CPU1 TCK resistor

Mandatory rework to replace FPGA KR RX AC Caps

Mandatory rework add a pull down to RSMRST

Mandatory rework to update VR FW

CPLD updates to address IFWI issue with 2 SKX FPGA\nCPUs populated

Required\nCPLD updates to address reset and FSC issues

InformationQuick Guide
BKC Artifactory Access

Link (SH server): https://ubit-artifactory-sh.intel.com

Link (OR server): https://ubit-artifactory-or.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website: https://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/RequestAccess/DisplayTree.aspx?TopNode=757719
  • Apply for the "Project viewer" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication

BKC One Stop Shop

Link: https://dcg-oss.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website: https://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/RequestAccess/DisplayTree.aspx?TopNode=829001
  • Navigate to:"BKC -- Purley"
  • Apply for the "User" or "Ingredient Owner" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication

Contact Person: Bei, Ling
